He said: 'Not at all, they are gentle giants. I was helping out a team of marine biologists conduct a survey on whale shark population estimates, to identify returning sharks year on year and to see growth rates of individuals.

'We were out for three days on the whole and it was on the first evening that I was able to have such an amazing interaction with the largest shark.'

The project is taking place at a secret location off the coast of Mexico.  

