He added: 'I have previously been in the water with the hammerhead along with various other sharks.

'As my passion and job revolves around amazing wildlife, I continue to seek encounters (both in the water and out) with all the most fantastic creatures I can.'

Unlike species such as the great white and tiger shark, the whale shark is very docile in the water and filters its food. 

Biologists do not know why the whale shark has any teeth as it does not use them for feeding, although they are thought to have evolved more than 90 million years ago. 

